Product images of Microsoft’s upcoming Surface devices have been posted by journalist and leaker Evan Blass on Twitter. Blass leaked images of what he said are the new Surface Pro 7, Surface Laptop 3, and an unnamed Surface 2-in-1 device ahead of Microsoft’s Surface hardware event on Wednesday 2 October. Blass also included the text: “Not pictured here: dual-screen Surface”, referencing the possible launch of Microsoft’s rumoured dual-screen Surface device. Previous reports have stated that this upcoming device could sport a pair of 9-inch screens, both of which would have a 4:3 aspect ratio. The new Surface Pro 7 could be available in five configurations, according to a recent report from WinFuture. It will reportedly be outfitted with 10th-generation Intel Core processors, as well as up to 512GB of solid-state storage and 16GB of RAM. The leaked images show that the Surface Laptop and Surface Pro 7 will feature similar designs to the previous generation of Surface hardware, although the new models could both include USB Type-C ports. The new ARM-powered 2-in-1 Surface device features a unique hinge design and thin bezels, setting it up as a possible competitor to Apple’s iPad Pro. Below are the leaked images of Microsoft’s upcoming Surface hardware: <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-321706" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Microsoft-Surface-Pro-7-4.jpg" alt="Microsoft Surface Pro 7 4" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Microsoft-Surface-Pro-7-4.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Microsoft-Surface-Pro-7-4-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Microsoft-Surface-Pro-7-4-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-321704" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uplo